The paper deals with optimization problems in a market setting, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of a multinomial logit model and position bias indicates that it could also belong to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The focus on retail and cultural markets suggests that it could belong to the categories of Marketing (cs.MKT) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
